Package nusri.fyp.demo.roboflow.data.request

Class GroundingDINOInferenceRequest

java.lang.Object
nusri.fyp.demo.roboflow.data.RoboflowRequestData
nusri.fyp.demo.roboflow.data.request.GroundingDINOInferenceRequest
public class GroundingDINOInferenceRequest extends RoboflowRequestData
Represents a request for Grounding DINO zero-shot predictions in the Roboflow API.
This class is used to send a request to the Roboflow API to perform zero-shot object detection using the Grounding DINO model, which predicts bounding boxes and associated labels without needing task-specific training data.

    • id

      private String id
      The unique identifier for the inference request.
      This field is used to reference and track the specific Grounding DINO inference request.

    • apiKey

      private String apiKey
      The API key associated with the request.
      This is required for authentication and to associate the request with a specific account.

    • usageBillable

      private Boolean usageBillable
      A flag indicating whether the inference usage is billable.
      This field specifies whether the request will incur charges.

    • start

      private Double start
      The start time of the inference request (in seconds).
      This field indicates when the Grounding DINO inference started.

    • source

      private String source
      The source of the image being processed.
      This can describe where the image originates from (e.g., "web", "camera", etc.).

    • sourceInfo

      private String sourceInfo
      Additional information about the image source.
      This can provide context or metadata about the image source.

    • modelId

      private String modelId
      The model ID used for the inference process.
      This field specifies which model will process the image for zero-shot prediction.

    • modelType

      private String modelType
      The model type used for the inference process.
      This field specifies the type of the model, which can help to differentiate between multiple models if applicable.

    • image

      private InferenceRequestImage image
      The image to be processed for zero-shot object detection.
      This field can be an array of objects or a single object representing the image data. The image will be processed to detect objects and their bounding boxes.

      private Boolean disablePreprocAutoOrient
      A flag to disable auto orientation preprocessing on the image.
      This flag determines if the image should be auto-oriented before processing.

    • disablePreprocContrast

    • text

      private List<String> text

      These queries help the model to predict specific objects based on the text input.

    • textThreshold

      The threshold for the text query predictions.
      This field specifies the minimum confidence required for a text-based prediction to be considered valid.

    • classAgnosticNms

      private Boolean classAgnosticNms
      A flag indicating whether class-agnostic Non-Maximum Suppression (NMS) should be used.
      When enabled, the NMS will not consider class labels when suppressing overlapping bounding boxes.
